description: Unique identifier for this part–warehouse record.
Date-time the record was last updated; often used for concurrency control.
Indicates whether this part is inactive at this warehouse.
Indicates if inventory quantities are tracked for this part at this warehouse.
Bin identifier within the warehouse where the part is stored.
Shelf code within the storage location for this part.
Row identifier within the storage area; likely a physical row indicator; confirm with SME.
Aisle identifier where the part’s storage location resides.
Free-text notes about stocking, handling, or location for this part at the warehouse.
Quantity currently on order from suppliers for this warehouse; likely on‑order amount; confirm with SME.
Standard reorder lot size or ordering multiple for this part at this warehouse.
Inventory level that triggers replenishment when reached.
Target maximum stocking level for this part in this warehouse.
Total inventory value for this part at this warehouse (on‑hand × unit cost); likely; confirm with SME.
Unit cost used for valuation of this part in this warehouse (e.g., average or last cost).
Quantity available to allocate or issue (on‑hand plus on‑order minus allocations).
Projected available quantity after scheduled receipts and allocations.
Physical on‑hand quantity in this warehouse.
Quantity scheduled to be allocated in future periods (planned commitments).
Quantity currently allocated or reserved for work orders and other demands.
Room or area code within the warehouse where the part is stored.
Display label or reference metadata for the room field; not business data.
Ordering increment/multiple for this part at this warehouse.
Display label or reference metadata for the partincr field; not business data.
Identifier of the warehouse associated with this record.
Display label or reference metadata for the warehouse field; not business data.
Identifier of the part/item this warehouse record refers to.
Display label or reference metadata for the part lookup/table; not business data.
Identifier for this record in the legacy source system.
Name of the legacy source table this record originated from.
Barcode associated with the part or its storage location in this warehouse.
Indicator/value used for initial inventory count of a newly added part; likely -1 means not yet counted; confirm with SME.
Cycle-count frequency code or interval for this part in this warehouse.
Default unit cost used when a specific warehouse cost is unavailable.
Quantity allocated via mobile transactions or mobile workflows.
Indicates inclusion in a rolling/cycle count program.
Next scheduled physical or cycle inventory count date for this part at this warehouse.
Most recent date this part was cycle counted or physically inventoried in this warehouse.
Date this part was last received into this warehouse.
Default work code to charge issues or route this part to; likely; confirm with SME.
Display label or reference metadata for the work code field; not business data.
Default work order to receive or charge this part to; likely; confirm with SME.
Display label or reference metadata for the work order field; not business data.
Identifier of the specific storage location or zone within the warehouse.
Display label or reference metadata for the storage_location field; not business data.
